  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\n_No response_\n\n### Describe the bug\n\ncurrently we record traces for _all_ fuzz runs.\r\n\r\ndepending on the size of the call and the fuzz case runs (256) default, this can grow very large very quickly. \r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/f817db31ab97a62fa635237da424c0e7105ce489/evm/src/fuzz/mod.rs#L57-L58\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/f817db31ab97a62fa635237da424c0e7105ce489/evm/src/fuzz/mod.rs#L345-L356\r\n\r\nBut only the last traces are selected for the final `TestResult`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/f817db31ab97a62fa635237da424c0e7105ce489/forge/src/runner.rs#L521-L528\r\n\r\nwe should only store 1 set of traces per Fuzztest or perhaps only record failed calls. the former could be implemented easily but only including the last CallTraceArena\r\n",
